snippet.textDisplay:
Considering it would be literally impossible to run every single road, only once, the figures you used are WAY under estimate.


Not that it's likely even possible to truly figure the numbers out, as even just finding the length of all dead-end roads to double their lengths alone, would be a monumental task.


After which you'd need to find some way to work out the optimal route to cover every single road in as few retreadings as possible.


I'd expect the number of miles of road, and the time to travel it, to be orders of magnitude higher than you used.
